<LandingPage title="CDCP Dentist in Surrey | Canary Smile Guide" description="Learn about CDCP coverage and book your appointment with our Surrey dental clinic.">
	<div class="hero">
		<h1>CDCP Dentist in Surrey</h1>
		<p class="intro">
			The Canadian Dental Care Plan (CDCP) helps eligible Canadians access essential dental care. As a participating CDCP dentist in Surrey, we are here to help you understand your coverage and get the care you need without the financial stress.
		</p>
	</div>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>What Does CDCP Cover?</h2>
		<p>The CDCP covers a variety of essential dental services to keep your teeth and gums healthy. Coverage may vary based on your eligibility, but generally includes:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Preventive Care:</strong> Exams, X-rays, and teeth cleaning.</li>
			<li><strong>Restorative Services:</strong> Fillings and root canal treatments.</li>
			<li><strong>Oral Surgery:</strong> Extractions (like pulling a wisdom tooth).</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<div class="faq">
			<details>
				<summary>Am I eligible for CDCP?</summary>
				<p>Eligibility depends on your family income and other criteria set by the government. Please check the official Government of Canada website for the latest details.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Do I have to pay out of pocket?</summary>
				<p>Depending on your adjusted family net income, you may have a co-payment. We will clearly explain any costs before treatment begins.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>How do I book a CDCP appointment in Surrey?</summary>
				<p>Simply contact us with your CDCP card and plan information. We'll handle the rest!</p>
			</details>
		</div>
	</section>

